title: FCO Strasbourg Koenigshoffen 06
text:
Football Club Olympique Strasbourg Koenigshoffen 06, known as Strasbourg Koenigshoffen or FCOSK06, is a <a href="Association%20football">football</a> club based in the and districts of <a href="RC%20Strasbourg%20Alsace">Strasbourg</a>, France. Founded in 1906, the club plays its home matches at the Stade Charles Frey. The club's colours are black and gold.
FCOSK06 played in the <a href="French%20Division%203%20%281971%E2%80%931993%29">Division 3</a> in the 1970s and 80s. The club has notably reached the round of 64 of the <a href="Coupe%20de%20France">Coupe de France</a> on several occasions. <a href="Didier%20Six">Didier Six</a> coached Koenigshoffen from 1997 to 1998, and <a href="Pascal%20Malbeaux">Pascal Malbeaux</a> served as the club's head coach and president.
